<subSubSection id="C3386570050BFF81FF32FE2598FB4195" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050BFF81FF32FE259D6F42FD" blockId="7.[189,310,400,426]" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">
<heading id="D0D58197050BFF81FF32FE259D6F42FD" bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FF32FE259D6F42FD" bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050BFF81FF32FE0B98FB4195" blockId="7.[188,1399,445,707]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FF32FE0B9DEC4280" authority="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira, 2021" authorityName="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,437,446,471]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmoreus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FF32FE0B9DEC4280" box="[189,437,446,471]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">Eusarcus marmoreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655792050BFF81FE35FE089E4D4280" box="[442,532,445,471]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from all species of the genus by having coxa IV with one transversal, proapical, trifurcated and truncated apophysis, with one dorsal apex higher than the other two ventrally-disposed apices. 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FDFDFDB49F35414D" authority="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira, 2021" authorityName="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2021" box="[626,876,513,538]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmoreus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FDFDFDB49F35414D" box="[626,876,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">Eusarcus marmoreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655792050BFF81FCFCFDB49F96414C" box="[883,975,513,539]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FBD9FDB49D5D416B" authority="(Mello-Leitao, 1932)" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1932" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berlae">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FBD9FDB4989B414D" box="[1110,1218,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">E. berlae</emphasis>
(Mello-Leitão, 1932)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FE9BFD969DA2416B" authority="Hara" authorityName="Hara" box="[276,507,546,572]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sergipanus">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FE9BFD969DE1416B" box="[276,440,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">E. sergipanus</emphasis>
Hara
</taxonomicName>
&amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, 2010, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FCB0FD9698D3416B" authority="(Roewer, 1949)" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[831,1162,546,572]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signatus">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FCB0FD969F9C416B" box="[831,965,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">E. signatus</emphasis>
(Roewer, 1949)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FB44FD969DBE4109" authority="(Soares &amp; Soares, 1946)" baseAuthorityName="Soares &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="1946" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sooretamae">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FB44FD96992E416B" box="[1227,1399,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">E. sooretamae</emphasis>
(Soares &amp; Soares, 1946)
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a proapical truncated apophysis at coxa IV but can be distinguished by the following characters: unarmed scutal area III, low ocularium with a median spine, femur IV with proventral and retroventral rows of acuminate tubercles increasing in size apically and trochanter IV with only one high (taller than trochanter width) promedian apophysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3386570050BFF81FF32FD5C9E314006" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050BFF81FF32FD5C9D1D4054" blockId="7.[189,1399,745,850]" box="[189,324,745,771]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">
<heading id="D0D58197050BFF81FF32FD5C9D1D4054" bold="true" box="[189,324,745,771]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FF32FD5C9D1D4054" bold="true" box="[189,324,745,771]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050BFF81FF32FCA09E314006" blockId="7.[189,1399,745,850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">
The specific epithet ʻ 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D78050BFF81FE31FCA39E1A4078" authorityName="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2021" box="[446,579,790,815]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmoreus">
<emphasis id="B956EAE9050BFF81FE31FCA39E1A4078" box="[446,579,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">marmoreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ means ʻof marbleʼ in Latin and refers to the lithology of the cave where the 
<typeStatus id="54998859050BFF81FEB8FC8D9D334005" box="[311,362,824,850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
specimen was found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
